{"id":"319163970_Dichotomies_structure_and_concentration_results","abstract":"We use probabilistic and topological methods to establish the following deviation inequality: For any normed space $X=(\\mathbb R^n ,\\|\\cdot\\| )$ there exists an invertible linear map $T:\\mathbb R^n \\to \\mathbb R^n$ with \\[ \\mathbb P\\left( \\big| \\|TG\\| -\\mathbb E\\|TG\\| \\big| > \\varepsilon \\mathbb E\\|TG\\| \\right) \\leq C\\exp \\left( -c\\max\\{ \\varepsilon^2, \\varepsilon \\} \\log \\left( \\frac{en}{ d(X,{\\cal U}_n)^2} \\right) \\right),\\quad \\varepsilon>0, \\] where $G$ is a standard $n$-dimensional Gaussian vector, $d(X, {\\cal U}_n)$ stands for the distance of $X$ to the class of all 1-unconditional $n$-dimensional normed spaces and $C,c>0$ are universal constants. As an application of the above, we show that for every $\\varepsilon\\in (0,1)$ and for every normed space $X=(\\mathbb R^n,\\|\\cdot\\|)$ there exists a $k$-dimensional subspace $E$ of $X$ which is $(1+\\varepsilon)$-Euclidean and $k\\geq c\\varepsilon \\log n/\\log\\frac{1}{\\varepsilon}$. This improves by a logarithmic on $\\varepsilon$ term the best previously known result due to G. Schechtman.","authors":["Grigorios Paouris","Petros Valettas"],"meta":["August 2017"],"references":["262185810_On_the_Diameter_of_Proportional_Sections_of_a_Symmetric_Convex_Body","226869715_Averages_of_norms_and_quasi-norms","2306536_Extremal_Problems_and_Isotropic_Positions_of_Convex_Bodies","318035616_On_the_tightness_of_Gaussian_concentration_for_convex_functions","316956155_The_variance_of_the_ell_pn-norm_of_the_Gaussian_vector_and_Dvoretzky's_theorem","315710622_Variance_estimates_and_almost_Euclidean_structure","313367456_Superconcentration_and_randomized_Dvoretzky's_theorem_for_spaces_with_1-unconditional_bases","309738262_A_small_deviation_inequality_for_convex_functions","285809848_A_new_proof_of_the_theorem_of_A_Dvoretzky_on_sections_of_convex_bodies","283279941_On_Dvoretzky's_theorem_for_subspaces_of_L_p","